					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-5299730#post-3725954</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-5299730/scp-3759#post-3725954</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Thu, 01 Mar 2018 22:30:40 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>fieldstone</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>1436137</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>This article <strong>has</strong> a narrative. It's a simple narrative - &quot;we found an island of ghost turtles, then a famous turtle died and appeared there (and we realized it's turtle heaven).&quot; If you look at the comments upthread, the simple cuteness of that story seems to be what's making it work for people despite its short length.</p> <p>Narrative doesn't mean an article is long or elaborate. It means the article describes a series of related events.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
